262
00:14:15,223 --> 00:14:16,523
Are you drunk?

263
00:14:17,623 --> 00:14:20,123
Totally wasted.

264
00:14:20,123 --> 00:14:24,523
I want to see you tomorrow, is that possible?

265
00:14:24,523 --> 00:14:28,023
Dad so drunk, I wonder if he's okay.

266
00:14:28,023 --> 00:14:30,849
He hasn't drunk at all and yet.

267
00:14:30,849 --> 00:14:34,853
Well, I guess this is a call he can't make unless he acts drunk.

268
00:14:47,128 --> 00:14:49,628
Do you remember this place?

269
00:14:49,628 --> 00:14:51,628
Of course.

270
00:14:51,628 --> 00:14:53,328
In summer ten years ago,

271
00:14:53,328 --> 00:14:58,877
two couples ran into each other.

272
00:14:59,828 --> 00:15:01,228
Takeoka?

273
00:15:01,228 --> 00:15:02,228
Mouri?

274
00:15:02,228 --> 00:15:04,883
Although we went to and were classmates of the same police academy,

275
00:15:04,883 --> 00:15:07,328
we were too embarrassed to talk about our wives,

276
00:15:07,328 --> 00:15:09,628
and never talked about them.

277
00:15:09,628 --> 00:15:12,228
Back then, we first got to talk to each other's wives.

278
00:15:12,228 --> 00:15:14,893
You got married when you were a student?

279
00:15:14,893 --> 00:15:16,028
Yes, sort of.

280
00:15:16,028 --> 00:15:17,228
We were childhood friends actually,

281
00:15:17,228 --> 00:15:18,897
or rather, ended up stuck with each other.

282
00:15:19,128 --> 00:15:20,899
What do you mean stuck with each other.

283
00:15:21,128 --> 00:15:23,928
We got to know each other in college.

284
00:15:23,928 --> 00:15:25,828
We both belonged to the drama club.

285
00:15:25,828 --> 00:15:27,928
You mean this awkward guy was in the drama club?

286
00:15:27,928 --> 00:15:31,928
Shut up! I used to be pretty keen back then.

287
00:15:34,913 --> 00:15:36,928
It's been ten years already.

288
00:15:36,928 --> 00:15:40,128
We were both young back then.

289
00:15:40,128 --> 00:15:42,528
Are you sure the culprit's going to come here?

290
00:15:42,528 --> 00:15:45,528
That's what pops told me.

291
00:15:45,528 --> 00:15:47,928
Just as I thought, he's having a tough time saying what he wants to.

292
00:15:47,928 --> 00:15:49,628
I guess I'll have to do it, then.

293
00:15:50,929 --> 00:15:53,428
The detective revives.

294
00:15:53,428 --> 00:15:56,128
My prayer's been answered.

295
00:15:56,128 --> 00:16:00,328
I've got to let pops solve this case himself.

296
00:16:02,228 --> 00:16:04,528
About the case we're investigating now...

297
00:16:05,928 --> 00:16:10,228
The culprit, after finding out that Mr. Kinugasa was murdered,

298
00:16:10,228 --> 00:16:11,928
planned everything.

299
00:16:11,928 --> 00:16:14,953
The plan was to kill Mr. Gamo making it look like

300
00:16:14,953 --> 00:16:16,428
he committed suicide,

301
00:16:16,428 --> 00:16:19,428
and setting his nephew, Mr. Arai up as the murderer,

302
00:16:19,428 --> 00:16:21,428
then killing him off too.

303
00:16:21,428 --> 00:16:23,228
But, if the culprit wanted to make it look like Gamo committed suicide

304
00:16:23,228 --> 00:16:26,028
and set Kyosuke Arai up as the killer,

305
00:16:26,028 --> 00:16:28,967
why did he have to bring Gamo all the way out to a far place

306
00:16:29,128 --> 00:16:31,828
and make it look like suicide?

307
00:16:31,828 --> 00:16:34,428
To set up an alibi.

308
00:16:34,428 --> 00:16:36,975
At 7 pm, the culprit, drives his own car

309
00:16:37,228 --> 00:16:40,979
and takes Mr. Gamo to the scene of the crime and kills him.

310
00:16:40,979 --> 00:16:44,728
He then hides his car in an abandoned warehouse

311
00:16:44,728 --> 00:16:46,428
near the Gamo residence.

312
00:16:46,428 --> 00:16:48,728
Then at 8 pm, the culprit poses as Mr. Gamo

313
00:16:48,728 --> 00:16:50,428
and gives me a call.

314
00:16:50,428 --> 00:16:53,628
He leaves the Gamo residence in Mr. Gamo's car

315
00:16:53,628 --> 00:16:56,028
and hides the car for the time being in the abandoned warehouse.

316
00:16:56,028 --> 00:16:57,428
He spends time with the person he had arrangements to see beforehand

317
00:16:57,428 --> 00:17:00,528
at 8:30 pm and stayed together until after midnight.

318
00:17:00,528 --> 00:17:01,528
After the meeting,

319
00:17:01,528 --> 00:17:04,128
he goes back to the abandoned warehouse to get Mr. Gamo's car

320
00:17:04,128 --> 00:17:07,005
to move it into the woods.

321
00:17:08,628 --> 00:17:11,428
So long as I'm talking to Mr. Gamo at 8 pm,

322
00:17:11,428 --> 00:17:15,028
Mr. Gamo had to have died after 9 pm.

323
00:17:15,028 --> 00:17:18,428
And the culprit also had an alibi during that time

324
00:17:18,428 --> 00:17:20,728
because he was with someone.

325
00:17:20,728 --> 00:17:23,328
In other words, you're saying that the last call you got from Gamo

326
00:17:23,328 --> 00:17:27,928
was the culprit mimicking his tone of voice?

327
00:17:27,928 --> 00:17:29,828
Right.

328
00:17:29,828 --> 00:17:31,528
But dad said he would never mistake

329
00:17:31,528 --> 00:17:33,528
the voice of his client for someone else.

330
00:17:33,528 --> 00:17:34,828
But, Mouri...

331
00:17:34,828 --> 00:17:37,035
Is it possible to deceive the ears of a former police detective

332
00:17:37,035 --> 00:17:39,028
and private detective such as you?

333
00:17:39,028 --> 00:17:43,041
If it was only that one time, I wouldn't have been deceived.

334
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:47,045
But the culprit had been repeating his trick from a half a month ago,

335
00:17:47,228 --> 00:17:49,728
in order to deceive me.

336
00:17:49,728 --> 00:17:52,028
From the first time he called.

337
00:17:52,028 --> 00:17:54,528
My name is Ryozo Gamo.

338
00:17:54,528 --> 00:17:56,428
I would like you to find somebody who can testify

339
00:17:56,428 --> 00:18:00,428
that I was at Akebonocho on the day of the crime.

340
00:18:00,428 --> 00:18:04,628
The one who kept calling me every night

341
00:18:04,628 --> 00:18:07,828
asking for results was not the real Gamo.

342
00:18:09,828 --> 00:18:16,128
I never ever met or talked to the real Mr. Gamo on the phone.

343
00:18:16,128 --> 00:18:17,528
Isn't that right?

344
00:18:17,528 --> 00:18:20,428
Drama boy back in your younger days, Takeoka.

345
00:18:22,428 --> 00:18:25,528
Mr. Gamo's characteristic appearance

346
00:18:25,528 --> 00:18:28,628
and voice were most convenient to copy, right?

347
00:18:28,628 --> 00:18:30,728
However, since I've known for quite some time,

348
00:18:30,728 --> 00:18:32,828
there was a risk that I would see through your disguise.

349
00:18:32,828 --> 00:18:35,928
That's why you deliberately came late that night

350
00:18:35,928 --> 00:18:37,428
when you came to see me.

351
00:18:37,428 --> 00:18:38,728
He says to give you his apologies,

352
00:18:38,728 --> 00:18:41,428
but to go ahead and start without him.

353
00:18:41,428 --> 00:18:46,128
You wanted to get me drunk and divert my concentration.

354
00:18:46,128 --> 00:18:47,105
-On top of that... -Mr. Gamo,

355
00:18:47,328 --> 00:18:48,728
I hope to be seeing you again soon.

356
00:18:48,728 --> 00:18:51,128
-Mr. Gamo. -I wouldn't doubt you,

357
00:18:51,128 --> 00:18:52,828
being that you virtually convinced

358
00:18:52,828 --> 00:18:54,728
all those around you of being someone else the way you did.

359
00:18:54,728 --> 00:18:58,428
It's only natural that the request made for finding a witness

360
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,528
to prove alibi didn't go well.

361
00:19:00,528 --> 00:19:02,228
Because after all,

362
00:19:02,228 --> 00:19:04,228
the content of the request was fake to begin with.

363
00:19:05,528 --> 00:19:07,128
In order to keep anybody from getting to you

364
00:19:07,128 --> 00:19:09,127
from the telephone records, you...

365
00:19:09,127 --> 00:19:12,228
It's Gamo. You haven't come up with anything yet?

366
00:19:12,228 --> 00:19:14,628
You waited for Mr. Gamo to take a bath

367
00:19:14,628 --> 00:19:17,528
and called me every night on a cordless phone

368
00:19:17,528 --> 00:19:19,928
or something that you secretly set up.

369
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:25,143
You've seen through everything.

370
00:19:25,143 --> 00:19:27,828
I guess, I was setting up useless tricks.

371
00:19:27,828 --> 00:19:30,128
Running into you at the horse race tracks

372
00:19:30,128 --> 00:19:32,328
wasn't a coincidence either, was it?

373
00:19:32,328 --> 00:19:33,528
No.

374
00:19:33,528 --> 00:19:35,153
Why?

375
00:19:35,328 --> 00:19:38,128
I'm sorry that I used you.

376
00:19:38,128 --> 00:19:39,528
Why'd you kill the two?

377
00:19:39,528 --> 00:19:41,528
Now, after five years have gone by!

378
00:19:46,328 --> 00:19:50,328
My wife... she died last month.

379
00:19:51,828 --> 00:19:55,173
After suffering with an illness for two years.

380
00:19:55,173 --> 00:20:02,628
She apologized to me just before she passed away.

381
00:20:02,628 --> 00:20:04,128
I'm sorry.

382
00:20:04,128 --> 00:20:05,728
About what?

383
00:20:07,428 --> 00:20:09,187
About five years ago.

384
00:20:13,428 --> 00:20:15,193
I was surprised

385
00:20:15,193 --> 00:20:18,028
that she had been regretting it all along

386
00:20:18,028 --> 00:20:23,201
that her testimony cornered me into resignation.

387
00:20:25,203 --> 00:20:28,928
But, I kept on believing her testimony.

388
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:30,528
I kept thinking that the witness for Gamo's alibi

389
00:20:30,528 --> 00:20:33,211
was just somebody that he had paid off to testify.

390
00:20:33,211 --> 00:20:36,328
And the day after her funeral,

391
00:20:36,328 --> 00:20:39,217
after finding that Sakae Kinugasa was murdered,

392
00:20:39,217 --> 00:20:41,219
I called Gamo.

393
00:20:42,328 --> 00:20:44,228
Wasn't it you?

394
00:20:44,228 --> 00:20:46,728
Just like you attacked the victim in the dark five years ago.

395
00:20:46,728 --> 00:20:49,227
This time it's wasn't me.

396
00:20:50,928 --> 00:20:54,128
I guess this is what you call the slip of the tongue.

397
00:20:54,128 --> 00:20:55,928
His said, "This time it's wasn't me".

398
00:20:55,928 --> 00:20:58,228
In other words, he did commit the previous crime.

399
00:20:59,228 --> 00:21:01,928
Natsuko's testimony was true.

400
00:21:04,128 --> 00:21:05,728
She spoke the truth,

401
00:21:05,728 --> 00:21:07,245
but I refused to believe her

402
00:21:07,245 --> 00:21:09,728
and she died apologizing to me.

403
00:21:09,728 --> 00:21:13,028
All I wanted to do was clear her feelings of grief.

404
00:21:15,628 --> 00:21:19,257
Mouri, make up with Eri.

405
00:21:20,228 --> 00:21:23,261
Don't be silly, blurting something like that out.

406
00:21:23,261 --> 00:21:24,528
Takeoka!

407
00:21:25,828 --> 00:21:27,265
Mr. Takeoka!

408
00:21:27,265 --> 00:21:29,267
Takeoka!

409
00:21:30,928 --> 00:21:33,028
Takeoka!

410
00:21:33,028 --> 00:21:34,228
Where are you?

411
00:21:34,228 --> 00:21:36,028
-Takeoka! -There he is!

412
00:21:36,028 --> 00:21:37,028
What?

413
00:21:38,528 --> 00:21:39,828
It can't be...

414
00:21:39,828 --> 00:21:41,028
Hold it!

415
00:21:42,728 --> 00:21:43,828
No way!

416
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:52,828
You're not dying on me.

417
00:21:52,828 --> 00:21:56,528
Live! You're making up for what you did!

418
00:21:56,528 --> 00:22:00,328
I'm not letting you die on me, Takeoka!

419
00:22:00,328 --> 00:22:01,299
Mouri!

420
00:22:03,628 --> 00:22:04,928
Mr. Takeoka!

421
00:22:06,728 --> 00:22:08,228
Mouri.

422
00:22:08,228 --> 00:22:09,728
Takeoka.

423
00:23:32,128 --> 00:23:35,128
Dad, you don't have to put the sign down for real.

424
00:23:35,128 --> 00:23:36,528
Pops.

425
00:23:36,528 --> 00:23:38,928
I always keep my word.

426
00:23:42,628 --> 00:23:45,403
A new one sure is good after all.

427
00:23:45,403 --> 00:23:47,405
You're not quitting being a detective?

428
00:23:47,405 --> 00:23:49,728
I never said anything like that.

429
00:23:50,728 --> 00:23:53,411
True, you only said was that you were going to bring the sign down.

430
00:23:53,411 --> 00:23:56,128
Being a detective is a lonesome job

431
00:23:56,128 --> 00:23:57,828
very usually misunderstood by others.

432
